================================================================================
Third-party dependencies
================================================================================

suren's core modules take no third-party dependencies. The packages geom, path,
paint, raster, scene, render, backend/cpu and backend/png are pure Go and depend
only on the standard library, so a build that uses only those pulls in nothing
listed below.

The dependencies here are reached only through the two quarantined modules,
each of which has its own go.mod:

  github.com/stohirov/suren/backend/gpu      (cgo; links wgpu-native)
  github.com/stohirov/suren/backend/window   (cgo; links a display library)

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
github.com/cogentcore/webgpu v0.23.0
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Go bindings for WebGPU. Required by backend/gpu.

License: Apache License 2.0.
  Verified from the LICENSE file in the module (module cache, v0.23.0), which
  carries the Apache-2.0 terms.

  FLAGGED: that LICENSE file states the Apache-2.0 terms but does not fill in a
  copyright holder — it ends at "END OF TERMS AND CONDITIONS" with no appendix
  and no "Copyright <year> <owner>" line, and the project README states no
  copyright either. The license is unambiguous; the holder is not recorded
  upstream, so no holder is asserted here.

This module vendors prebuilt static libraries (wgpu/lib/<os>/<arch>/
libwgpu_native.a) which backend/gpu statically links via cgo. Their provenance
and terms are below.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
wgpu-native (github.com/gfx-rs/wgpu-native)
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
The native WebGPU implementation (Vulkan / Metal / D3D12 / GL). Not a Go module
dependency: it enters the build as the prebuilt libwgpu_native.a static archives
vendored inside cogentcore/webgpu, and is statically linked into any binary that
imports backend/gpu.

License: dual-licensed Apache License 2.0 OR MIT, at the user's option.
  Verified from the upstream repository (github.com/gfx-rs/wgpu-native), which
  publishes both LICENSE.APACHE and LICENSE.MIT.

  FLAGGED: the vendored .a archives inside cogentcore/webgpu@v0.23.0 carry no
  license file, copyright notice, or version stamp of their own. The terms above
  are the upstream project's, read from upstream — not from the binaries as
  shipped. The exact wgpu-native revision these archives were built from is not
  recorded in the module; the README states only that they are built via the
  repository's own GitHub Actions workflow. If precise provenance matters for
  your distribution, pin and rebuild from source rather than relying on this
  attribution.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
