================================================================================
Scope of this file
================================================================================

Every license above was verified by reading the LICENSE file or SPDX header in
the module as it is actually resolved into the build, except where marked
FLAGGED, where the reason is stated. No license terms here were inferred from a
package name, a badge, or convention.

Two categories are deliberately absent, because appearing in the module graph is
not the same as being linked:

  - Build-time-only tools reached through cogentcore/webgpu's own module graph
    (gofumpt, golang.org/x/tools, golang.org/x/mod, go-cmp, iancoleman/strcase,
    the modernc.org packages, remyoudompheng/bigfft, lukechampine.com/uint128).
    They appear in `go list -m all` for backend/gpu and are linked into no suren
    binary.

  - github.com/go-gl/glfw. It appears in backend/gpu's module graph via
    cogentcore/webgpu's wgpuglfw package, which suren does not import: verified
    absent from `go list -deps` for backend/gpu. suren renders offscreen and
    reaches a window through backend/window (Ebiten) instead. If Phase 6b's
    native surface present lands, it will link glfw behind the `gpupresent`
    build tag and this file must gain an entry for it.
